ures `force=true` reinstalls still don't duplicate the trusted command.\\n\\n**Clean uninstall with `isEntireTrustedCommand`**: Rather than only removing the exact command that was installed, the uninstall function removes *both* production and local-dev variants. This handles the case where a user switches modes — `UninstallHooks` always cleans up completely regardless of which mode was used during install.\\n`─────────────────────────────────────────────────`\\n\\nAll done. Here's a summary of the changes:\\n\\n**`cmd/entire/cli/agent/kiro/hooks.go`**:\\n- Added constants: `vscodeSettingsDir`, `vscodeSettingsFile`, `trustedCommandsKey`, `prodTrustedCommand`\\n- Added helpers: `trustedCommand()`, `isEntireTrustedCommand()`, `trustedCommandsPresent()`, `installTrustedCommands()`, `uninstallTrustedCommands()`\\n- `InstallHooks`: Now calls `installTrustedCommands()` after IDE hooks, and includes `trustedCommandsPresent()` in the idempotency check\\n- `UninstallHooks`: Now calls `uninstallTrustedCommands()` after removing IDE hooks\\n\\n**`cmd/entire/cli/agent/kiro/hooks_test.go`**:\\n- 8 new tests covering: fresh install, existing settings preservation, local-dev mode, idempotency (no duplicates), preserving user trusted commands, idempotency check detecting missing trusted commands, uninstall cleanup, and no-settings-file graceful handling\"}],\"stop_reason\":\"end_turn\",\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":1,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":104,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":99243,\"output_tokens\":551,\"server_tool_use\":{\"web_search_requests\":0,\"web_fetch_requests\":0},\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":104,\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0},\"inference_geo\":\"\",\"iterations\":[],\"speed\":\"standard\"}},\"requestId\":\"req_011CYhAMn3ziyw11KJCV9Rb5\",\"type\":\"assistant\",\"uuid\":\"f7831cae-090d-4cbc-a336-7634c63d07b0\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-04T01:20:54.890Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"f7831cae-090d-4cbc-a33